ACT:
 East Punjab Urban Rent Restriction Act, 1948--Section 13(3)(a)(i)(a) read with Section 2 (a), (d), (g) and (h)--Eviction of "scheduled building" for personal need--Held, all buildings fall into two categories, non- residential and residential--'Scheduled building' in Section 2(h) is a kind of 'residential building' and ground of eviction for personal need available--Amendment Acts of 1956, 1957, 1966 and 1985--Section 13A.
 East Punjab Urban Rent Restriction Act 1948--Sections 13, 13A and 2(a), (d), (g) and (h)--Interpretation of statutes--Principle of harmonious construction--Omission of "scheduled building" by amendment in 1956, and its inclusion in provisions inserted by the 1985 amendment--Held, retention of "scheduled" in the provision when "residential building" includes scheduled building considered superfluous--Inserted in 1985 Amendment to avoid con- troversies.
 
